In a survey of viruses in [@vegetable crops#Plant*] in Western Samoa, [$squash mosaic comovirus#Virus*] was recorded for the first time infecting [$Citrullus lanatus#Plant*], [@Cucurbita maxima#Plant*] and [@Trichosanthes cucumerina var.anguina#Plant*].
Other new host records for Western Samoa were [@papaya ringspot potyvirus#Virus*] infecting [$C.maxima#Plant*] and [$Cucumis sativus#Plant*], [$zucchini yellow mosaic potyvirus#Virus*] infecting these two hosts and also [$Momordica charantia#Plant*] and [$Capsicum annuum#Plant*], and [$cucumber mosaic cucumovirus#Virus*] infecting [$Benincasa hispida#Plant*] and [@Psophocarpus tetragonolobus#Plant*].